            "title": "Investor Hakimian warns U.S. economy under Trump's 2nd term is struggling with growth from government spending, tech expansion.",
            "id": "dd85559d-272d-46b7-9092-0231102083ba",
            "description": "Hedge fund manager Spencer Hakimian has raised concerns about the state of the U.S. economy during President Donald Trump's second term. In a recent post, Hakimian described the economy as \"barely hanging on by a string\" six months into \"Trump 2.0\", attributing any growth to significant government spending increasing by over 10% annually, as well as the unrestricted expansion of big tech companies. He highlighted that the economy is mainly being driven by Washington DC and San Francisco, with other regions and sectors facing pressure. Hakimian emphasized the reliance on government spending and big tech, noting the challenges faced by other sectors. He also mentioned that the country is witnessing unchecked growth in these areas, indicating potential risks.",
